This paper investigates the frequency distribution of error messages in programming, which is a topic related to software engineering (cs.SE) and programming languages (cs.PL). The paper also uses statistical methods to analyze the data, which falls under machine learning (cs.LG) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Additionally, the paper may be relevant to natural language processing (cs.CL) as it deals with analyzing and categorizing text data.
